I always knew I was a fan of these leggings, however, today completely took me by surprise. As I was walking across campus to my local Kwik Trip, I biffed it on some ice and fell on all fours. My entire shin was covered in snow and dirt and I could feel pain in my knee. When I went back to my dorm, I saw the huge scrape and bruise I suffered from the fall. BUT MY LEGGINGS? column6: These leggings were my first purchase from Lululemon. Initially, I was really excited and scared at the same time to buy them (since they are supposed to be good quality, but so expensive). However, I ordered a size up because I find that their Luon fabric is see-through in my size. After working up the nerve to buy them, I was pretty disappointed. I wanted to love these leggings, since they had the high waist that I like and were made of Luon, my favourite fabric from this brand (keep in mind I also spent about 2 hours in the store trying on different makes and fabrics to figure out which one I liked best). After maybe 3 wears, the leggings began to pill, stretched out and it almost feels as though the material thinned out because they don't hold me in as well and leave me to constantly having to pull them up. column1: Wunder Under Super High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon Online Only 28"
column5: Never been more disappointed with this brand
column6:
I have 2 pairs of the original Wunder Unders from about 7 years ago, that are still in great condition, but I wanted to get a pair in the high-rise. I bought a pair, but I will be returning them.
First of all, let me just say how much rage I have for the fact that the length has changed from 31" to 28". The new length looks so so stupid on me. They're about 1" too short so they look like they shrunk in the wash. I'm not even THAT tall (5'8"), but guess it was more important for lulu to save on all that free hemming, than to cater to their taller clientele. It would have been nice if they offered regular, short and tall options instead of changing the length altogether.
The second qualm I have is that THESE. ARE. SEE. THROUGH. I didn't notice in the change room, but the light was different at home and you can see everything. I feel sick to my stomach that I spent over $100 on pants that are see through. I've loved lulu for years, and it would be nice to be able to replace some of my older stuff with new, but the quality isn't there anymore, and I'm a bit at a loss for what to do. I want new Wunder Unders. But I'm not paying that much for a lousy product.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hi gingerninja,\nThanks for taking the time to share your feedback. We would love to get a bit more information on your experience, and look into some options. An email is headed your way, so keep an eye out.', 'LL_response_date': 'October 18, 2017'}
